ersation.com/files/586880/original/file-20240409-18-xeet5s.png?q=30&amp;usm=12&amp;cs=strip&amp;w=2560&amp;auto=format&amp;rect=0%2C48%2C607%2C607&amp;fit=crop"/></div></a></div></section><p class="max-w-screen-lg font-serif lg:text-xl"></p><section class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:gap-6 sm:grid-cols-4 mb-4" data-testid="grid"><div class="group relative flex overflow-hidden col-span-2 sm:col-span-1 border-t pt-4" data-testid="ImmutableGridSlot"><a href="https://theconversation.com/how-conspiracy-theories-help-to-maintain-vladimir-putins-grip-on-power-in-russia-225703" class="group flex w-full gap-2 sm:flex-col-reverse sm:justify-end"><section class="flex flex-col items-start gap-2 sm:basis-auto basis-3/4"><span class="group-hover:text-indigo-600 group-hover:underline"><h5 class="font-bold font-sans-heading text-base leading-5 lg:text-lg lg:leading-6"><span>How conspiracy theories help to maintain Vladimir Putin’s grip on power in Russia</span></h5></span><span class="inline-flex max-w-full items-center gap-1 truncate rounded-full py-1 px-3 font-sans text-sm  hover:bg-black bg-black/70 text-white hover:bg-black"><span class="truncate">Listen</span><div class="ml-0.5 -mr-1.5"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" data-slot="icon" class="h-3.5 w-3.5"><path d="M7 4a3 3 0 0 1 6 0v6a3 3 0 1 1-6 0V4Z"></path><path d="M5.5 9.643a.75.75 0 0 0-1.5 0V10c0 3.06 2.29 5.585 5.25 5.954V17.5h-1.5a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h4.5a.75.75 0 0 0 0-1.5h-1.5v-1.546A6.001 6.001 0 0 0 16 10v-.357a.75.75 0 0 0-1.5 0V10a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-9 0v-.357Z"></path></svg></div></span></section><div class="relative hidden aspect-square basis-1/4 sm:aspect-video sm:basis-auto md:block"><img alt="A big screen in a street showing Vladimir Russia. " loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="object-cover" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent;background-size:cover;background-position:50% 5